│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1.          │
│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe verifier error indicates a dominance violation: │
│ an insertelement instruction does not dominate a shufflevector that uses it.  │
│ Specifically, SLP is building a vector via a sequence of CreateInsertElement  │
│ calls and then combining it with a Root via CreateShuffle. If the shuffle is  │
│ emitted in an earlier block (or earlier position) than where the inserts were │
│ placed, the shufflevector ends up using a value that does not dominate it.    │
│ This matches the symptom: \"%5 = insertelement ...\" and then \"%3 =          │
│ shufflevector ... %5 ...\" where %3 is placed before %5 in the IR.\n\n2.      │
│ Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe log shows the crash happens during IR verification, │
│ and the first transformed IR seen by the verifier includes a shufflevector    │
│ that references an insertelement. The SLP pass is responsible for creating    │
│ both. From the code, BoUpSLP::gather constructs the new vector using          │
│ Builder.CreateInsertElement and then possibly calls CreateShuffle(Root, Vec,  │
│ Mask). There is no adjustment of the Builder insertion point in gather based  │
│ on Root. If Root resides in a different block or earlier position, the        │
│ inserts may be emitted after Root.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nIn             │
│ BoUpSLP::gather, we use the current Builder insertion point without ensuring  │
│ it is compatible with where the final CreateShuffle (which may be created at  │
│ the insertion point or at Root's location, depending on the callback) will be │
│ placed. Since gather may be called to build a vector to be combined with      │
│ Root, and Root can be an existing instruction in an earlier block, the        │
│ created insertelement instructions can end up inserted after the use point,   │
│ violating dominance. The code lacks setting the insertion point relative to   │
│ Root within gather. We already have logic elsewhere                           │
│ (setInsertPointAfterBundle) to ensure dominance for other vectorization       │
│ paths, but gather does not adjust the insertion point when Root is            │
│ provided.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nWe should set the Builder insertion  │
│ point at the beginning of BoUpSLP::gather when a Root is provided and is an   │
│ Instruction, to ensure all CreateInsertElement operations dominate the        │
│ subsequent CreateShuffle combining with Root. This is a minimal, targeted     │
│ fix.\n\nEdit at llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp lines         │
│ 14914-14938:\nInsert the following at the start of BoUpSLP::gather, right     │
│ after the function signature and before any insertion logic:\n\n  // Ensure   │
│ inserts dominate the final shuffle that uses them.\n  if (Root) {\n    if     │
│ (auto *RootI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Root)) {\n      // Place inserts before  │
│ Root to guarantee dominance.\n      Builder.SetInsertPoint(RootI);\n          │
│ Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(RootI->getDebugLoc());\n    }\n               │
│ }\n\nRationale:\n- By moving the insertion point to just before Root when     │
│ Root is an instruction, all created insertelement instructions will be placed │
│ before the shufflevector that combines with Root, ensuring dominance.\n- This │
│ keeps the transformation local and avoids changing scheduling decisions       │
│ elsewhere.\n- It aligns with existing practices in the pass where insertion   │
│ points are carefully set (e.g., setInsertPointAfterBundle).\n\n5.             │
│ Conclusion:\nThe crash is due to insertelement instructions being emitted     │
│ after their use in a shufflevector, violating dominance. Setting the          │
│ IRBuilder insertion point to Root when available inside BoUpSLP::gather       │
│ ensures that all inserts dominate the subsequent shuffle. This fix should     │
│ prevent the verifier from detecting broken dominance and resolve the          │
│ SIGABRT."})                                                                   │
