│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The verifier error indicates a dominance violation: an insertelement          │
│ instruction does not dominate a shufflevector that uses it. Specifically, SLP │
│ is building a vector via a sequence of CreateInsertElement calls and then     │
│ combining it with a Root via CreateShuffle. If the shuffle is emitted in an   │
│ earlier block (or earlier position) than where the inserts were placed, the   │
│ shufflevector ends up using a value that does not dominate it. This matches   │
│ the symptom: "%5 = insertelement ..." and then "%3 = shufflevector ... %5     │
│ ..." where %3 is placed before %5 in the IR.                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The log shows the crash happens during IR verification, and the first         │
│ transformed IR seen by the verifier includes a shufflevector that references  │
│ an insertelement. The SLP pass is responsible for creating both. From the     │
│ code, BoUpSLP::gather constructs the new vector using                         │
│ Builder.CreateInsertElement and then possibly calls CreateShuffle(Root, Vec,  │
│ Mask). There is no adjustment of the Builder insertion point in gather based  │
│ on Root. If Root resides in a different block or earlier position, the        │
│ inserts may be emitted after Root.                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ In BoUpSLP::gather, we use the current Builder insertion point without        │
│ ensuring it is compatible with where the final CreateShuffle (which may be    │
│ created at the insertion point or at Root's location, depending on the        │
│ callback) will be placed. Since gather may be called to build a vector to be  │
│ combined with Root, and Root can be an existing instruction in an earlier     │
│ block, the created insertelement instructions can end up inserted after the   │
│ use point, violating dominance. The code lacks setting the insertion point    │
│ relative to Root within gather. We already have logic elsewhere               │
│ (setInsertPointAfterBundle) to ensure dominance for other vectorization       │
│ paths, but gather does not adjust the insertion point when Root is provided.  │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ We should set the Builder insertion point at the beginning of BoUpSLP::gather │
│ when a Root is provided and is an Instruction, to ensure all                  │
│ CreateInsertElement operations dominate the subsequent CreateShuffle          │
│ combining with Root. This is a minimal, targeted fix.                         │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit at llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp lines 14914-14938:    │
│ Insert the following at the start of BoUpSLP::gather, right after the         │
│ function signature and before any insertion logic:                            │
│                                                                               │
│   // Ensure inserts dominate the final shuffle that uses them.                │
│   if (Root) {                                                                 │
│     if (auto *RootI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Root)) {                          │
│       // Place inserts before Root to guarantee dominance.                    │
│       Builder.SetInsertPoint(RootI);                                          │
│       Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(RootI->getDebugLoc());                  │
│     }                                                                         │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Rationale:                                                                    │
│ - By moving the insertion point to just before Root when Root is an           │
│ instruction, all created insertelement instructions will be placed before the │
│ shufflevector that combines with Root, ensuring dominance.                    │
│ - This keeps the transformation local and avoids changing scheduling          │
│ decisions elsewhere.                                                          │
│ - It aligns with existing practices in the pass where insertion points are    │
│ carefully set (e.g., setInsertPointAfterBundle).                              │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash is due to insertelement instructions being emitted after their use  │
│ in a shufflevector, violating dominance. Setting the IRBuilder insertion      │
│ point to Root when available inside BoUpSLP::gather ensures that all inserts  │
│ dominate the subsequent shuffle. This fix should prevent the verifier from    │
│ detecting broken dominance and resolve the SIGABRT.                           │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
